# Native.js Framework Rules

## No External Libraries

- Do NOT use any external JavaScript libraries
- Use only native browser APIs supported by: Safari, Chrome, Firefox, Safari iOS, Chrome Android
- Reference MDN (mdn.github.io) for API compatibility

## Source Code

- All framework code MUST be written in TypeScript
- Source files live in `src/` directory
- Use Bun bundler for compilation

## Web Components

- Use native Web Components API (Custom Elements v1)
- Do NOT use Shadow DOM by default
- Components should support children by default
- Register custom elements with `n-` prefix

## Examples

- Every new feature MUST have a corresponding example
- Examples live in `examples/` directory
- Examples demonstrate real-world usage patterns

## Browser Compatibility

Before using any API, verify support on:
- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Safari iOS (latest)
- Chrome Android (latest)
